1
00:00:03,360 --> 00:00:04,477
(Qingyixuan Antiques Store)

2
00:00:04,560 --> 00:00:06,640
You don't want
to do business with us, do you?

3
00:00:06,880 --> 00:00:08,920
Do you know you're embezzling assets?

4
00:00:09,160 --> 00:00:10,360
It's hard for me too.

5
00:00:10,480 --> 00:00:13,460
It's...
I've been scolding him for one morning.

6
00:00:13,560 --> 00:00:15,160
Who did you sell to?
Go and get it back.

7
00:00:15,800 --> 00:00:18,506
The main problem is that
I don't know who I sold it to.

8
00:00:18,590 --> 00:00:19,670
He's not a regular customer.

9
00:00:23,720 --> 00:00:24,720
How about the CCTV?

10
00:00:25,320 --> 00:00:27,320
It's already broken,
merely for display purposes.

11
00:00:40,840 --> 00:00:41,840
Not me.

12
00:00:43,880 --> 00:00:44,880
Yeah, right.

13
00:00:46,680 --> 00:00:48,800
No, it's really...

14
00:00:49,080 --> 00:00:50,757
It has nothing to do with me.
Isn't that right, boss?

15
00:00:50,840 --> 00:00:51,840
I'm...

16
00:00:51,920 --> 00:00:52,960
Boss.

17
00:00:53,040 --> 00:00:54,240
Get your staff to check it out.

18
00:00:54,960 --> 00:00:55,960
You have to get it back.

19
00:00:56,480 --> 00:00:57,597
You are truly black-hearted.

20
00:00:57,680 --> 00:00:59,240
Just 100,000 yuan. You're...

21
00:00:59,520 --> 00:01:01,757
-I sold it.
-You're really...

22
00:01:01,840 --> 00:01:03,200
I don't want to comment on you.

23
00:01:16,120 --> 00:01:17,840
Where is the Chenpi water
that I asked you to soak up for me?

24
00:01:19,880 --> 00:01:20,880
I beg your pardon.

25
00:01:22,040 --> 00:01:23,040
What's wrong with you?

26
00:01:23,200 --> 00:01:24,200
Chenpi...

27
00:01:25,040 --> 00:01:26,080
You're so distracted.

28
00:01:31,320 --> 00:01:32,320
Xin Zheng,

29
00:01:33,400 --> 00:01:35,120
our son's pendant

30
00:01:36,440 --> 00:01:38,960
is really gone this time.

31
00:01:43,400 --> 00:01:44,480
It's gone this time?

32
00:01:45,880 --> 00:01:46,880
How about the previous times?

33
00:01:48,320 --> 00:01:49,320
Well...

34
00:01:50,680 --> 00:01:52,960
I don't know.

35
00:02:13,920 --> 00:02:15,560
Where is your agarwood pendant?

36
00:02:16,480 --> 00:02:17,560
Where did you go yesterday?

37
00:02:18,400 --> 00:02:19,400
I don't know.

38
00:02:19,960 --> 00:02:21,320
Don't you know where you've been?

39
00:02:27,040 --> 00:02:28,040
I'm talking to you.

40
00:02:36,120 --> 00:02:37,120
Ren Tian Zhen.

41
00:02:37,320 --> 00:02:38,760
You are almost 28 years old.

42
00:02:38,960 --> 00:02:40,680
When will you be able
to live like a human being?

43
00:02:43,320 --> 00:02:45,037
Do you know how precious
that pendant means to you?

44
00:02:45,120 --> 00:02:47,597
That's the expectation of our
several generations of family for you!

45
00:02:47,680 --> 00:02:48,680
Xin Zheng.

46
00:02:50,713 --> 00:02:52,926
-Mum.
-Can't you talk nicely?

47
00:02:54,200 --> 00:02:55,200
Explain to your grandma!

48
00:02:55,960 --> 00:02:57,120
This is not the first time, right?

49
00:03:01,320 --> 00:03:02,480
Where did you go yesterday?

50
00:03:04,040 --> 00:03:05,120
Be honest!

51
00:03:05,480 --> 00:03:06,480
Xin Zheng.

52
00:03:07,040 --> 00:03:09,040
Be patient when
you're educating your son.

53
00:03:09,600 --> 00:03:11,960
Give him some time to grow.

54
00:03:12,320 --> 00:03:13,760
Everyone's point of enlightenment

55
00:03:14,200 --> 00:03:15,320
is different.

56
00:03:15,920 --> 00:03:17,120
There are not many wunderkinder like you

57
00:03:17,320 --> 00:03:20,320
who have been
persistent in their ambition.

58
00:03:21,760 --> 00:03:23,120
I'd rather Tian Zhen

59
00:03:23,600 --> 00:03:25,120
be warming the bench for ten years.

60
00:03:26,400 --> 00:03:28,560
In the end, he will be a late bloomer.

61
00:03:29,840 --> 00:03:30,840
Master,

62
00:03:31,480 --> 00:03:33,200
can I beg you for one thing?

63
00:03:34,920 --> 00:03:38,120
When I teach my son,
please don't protect him.

64
00:03:42,320 --> 00:03:43,320
I don't expect him

65
00:03:43,760 --> 00:03:45,480
to be a late bloomer anymore.

66
00:03:46,200 --> 00:03:48,040
I'm afraid he's useless.

67
00:03:52,560 --> 00:03:53,760
He is my only son.

68
00:03:54,200 --> 00:03:57,320
I hope
you'll be honest with your parents.

69
00:03:58,040 --> 00:03:59,200
To be an honest man!

70
00:04:00,560 --> 00:04:01,517
Your dad is right.

71
00:04:01,600 --> 00:04:02,800
Tell the truth

72
00:04:03,720 --> 00:04:05,117
and admit your mistake.

73
00:04:05,200 --> 00:04:08,117
From now on,
you won't leave anything behind.

74
00:04:08,200 --> 00:04:10,957
Mum, it's not a matter
of leaving things behind.

75
00:04:11,040 --> 00:04:12,120
You say that you lecture your child,

76
00:04:12,560 --> 00:04:14,400
but you don't even know how old I am.

77
00:04:15,040 --> 00:04:15,957
I'm 25 years old this year,

78
00:04:16,040 --> 00:04:17,200
I'm not 28 years old.

79
00:04:18,040 --> 00:04:21,000
You either ignore me or lecture me.

80
00:04:21,600 --> 00:04:23,160
There is no place for me
in your lofty ideals

81
00:04:23,280 --> 00:04:24,597
of teaching, nurturing people,

82
00:04:24,680 --> 00:04:26,040
and carrying on the tradition.

83
00:04:39,480 --> 00:04:40,480
What's up?

84
00:04:47,760 --> 00:04:49,600
I took his pendant.

85
00:04:51,840 --> 00:04:53,160
What are you doing with his pendant?

86
00:04:55,840 --> 00:04:57,280
I took it to the pawn shop and sold it.

87
00:04:58,000 --> 00:05:00,200
I need money recently.

88
00:05:09,440 --> 00:05:10,600
What do you do with the money?

89
00:05:12,280 --> 00:05:15,080
When I worked as
a delivery rider, I was

90
00:05:16,280 --> 00:05:17,637
playing poker with them.

91
00:05:17,720 --> 00:05:18,720
And then

92
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:20,797
I owed them a lot of money.

93
00:05:20,880 --> 00:05:22,077
I thought that pendant

94
00:05:22,160 --> 00:05:23,597
was worth a lot of money.

95
00:05:23,680 --> 00:05:24,680
Therefore, I

96
00:05:25,320 --> 00:05:26,320
took it.

97
00:05:28,600 --> 00:05:30,960
Master, I've been evil again.

98
00:05:32,120 --> 00:05:33,117
I'm sorry.

99
00:05:33,200 --> 00:05:34,277
Why don't you punish me?

100
00:05:34,360 --> 00:05:36,840
I'll find a way
to redeem that pendant by then, can I?

101
00:05:38,200 --> 00:05:40,200
What a reckless act!

102
00:05:41,880 --> 00:05:43,040
Get out and get into a horse stance!

103
00:06:31,720 --> 00:06:33,000
You scared me out of my wits!

104
00:06:33,480 --> 00:06:35,557
Take this to Tou Tou.

105
00:06:35,640 --> 00:06:37,760
No one can squat like this for a day.

106
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:40,320
No need, Sun Tou Tou is very tricky.

107
00:06:41,200 --> 00:06:44,640
It's true if you say she would
play tricks back in the day.

108
00:06:44,760 --> 00:06:45,760
But now,

109
00:06:46,280 --> 00:06:47,760
she can really squat
like this for a day.

110
00:06:50,720 --> 00:06:51,720
Give it to her.

111
00:06:52,040 --> 00:06:53,480
She won't take it
if I'm the one who gives her.

112
00:07:18,000 --> 00:07:18,997
What are you doing?

113
00:07:19,080 --> 00:07:20,077
You can sit for a while
if you are tired.

114
00:07:20,160 --> 00:07:20,957
I'll cover for you.

115
00:07:21,040 --> 00:07:22,477
I'm not tired at all.

116
00:07:22,560 --> 00:07:24,480
Hurry up and stay aside.

117
00:07:24,760 --> 00:07:25,557
Can you?

118
00:07:25,640 --> 00:07:26,640
I can do it.

119
00:07:26,760 --> 00:07:28,480
Do you think you're Wonder Woman?

120
00:07:28,760 --> 00:07:30,880
If you keep squatting like this,
your thighs can't take it.

121
00:07:31,080 --> 00:07:33,040
Don't be stubborn.
Can't I try it?

122
00:07:33,119 --> 00:07:34,119
Go aside.

123
00:07:34,640 --> 00:07:35,640
Go aside.

124
00:07:44,480 --> 00:07:45,480
I'm with you.

125
00:07:47,920 --> 00:07:49,320
Are you an idiot?

126
00:07:50,560 --> 00:07:53,677
If your dad sees it, he will know
I'm taking the fall for you.

127
00:07:53,760 --> 00:07:55,320
Then my drama just now will be wasted.

128
00:07:55,600 --> 00:07:57,040
Can you get in?

129
00:07:57,440 --> 00:07:59,200
Do you think my dad doesn't know?

130
00:07:59,640 --> 00:08:01,040
You can assume
I'm practicing next to you.

131
00:08:01,760 --> 00:08:03,560
I won't let you practice alone.

132
00:08:04,040 --> 00:08:06,320
If I practiced well, it's good to
improve the skill of observing.

133
00:08:34,920 --> 00:08:36,120
Tou Tou

134
00:08:36,360 --> 00:08:37,960
is getting calmer.

135
00:08:40,520 --> 00:08:42,040
She has squatted for so long
without rest.

136
00:08:46,480 --> 00:08:47,680
It's a bit sunny.

137
00:08:49,040 --> 00:08:50,040
I'm afraid

138
00:08:51,360 --> 00:08:52,680
she will be dehydrated later.

139
00:08:55,520 --> 00:08:56,960
Tian Zhen is squatting
together with her as well.

140
00:09:16,800 --> 00:09:18,480
How heavy can you lift?

141
00:09:19,480 --> 00:09:20,480
55 kilograms.

142
00:09:21,280 --> 00:09:22,280
All right.

143
00:09:23,360 --> 00:09:24,360
That's okay.

144
00:09:25,960 --> 00:09:28,160
You go in and take some rest.

145
00:09:29,360 --> 00:09:31,680
If I collapse later,
you can carry me into the house.

146
00:09:32,800 --> 00:09:34,840
I tell you to eat less before this.

147
00:09:35,240 --> 00:09:36,840
What if I can't carry you later?

148
00:09:37,120 --> 00:09:39,600
What does it have to do
with how much I eat?

149
00:09:42,520 --> 00:09:43,600
Just drag me like a dead dog.

150
00:09:43,960 --> 00:09:45,520
I suppose you know
how to drag me in, right?

151
00:09:54,240 --> 00:09:55,240
Xin Zheng,

152
00:09:58,040 --> 00:09:59,037
don't be angry.

153
00:09:59,120 --> 00:10:00,037
Look at them.

154
00:10:00,120 --> 00:10:03,360
Aren't they apologising to you
in a different way?

155
00:10:08,840 --> 00:10:10,597
You know where your son's pendant is,

156
00:10:10,680 --> 00:10:12,120
don't you?

157
00:10:15,360 --> 00:10:16,680
You and your son

158
00:10:17,360 --> 00:10:18,480
have a tacit understanding.

159
00:10:19,600 --> 00:10:20,600
Am I right?

160
00:10:24,840 --> 00:10:28,840
He used to travel every year.

161
00:10:29,960 --> 00:10:32,600
Since you nagged him,

162
00:10:33,280 --> 00:10:35,160
and let him fend for himself,

163
00:10:35,720 --> 00:10:37,120
don't spend our money,

164
00:10:37,480 --> 00:10:40,120
since then,
he started to leave things behind.

165
00:10:41,160 --> 00:10:42,240
Is that my fault?

166
00:10:42,720 --> 00:10:43,840
That's not what I meant.

167
00:10:44,240 --> 00:10:46,877
But our son was right too.

168
00:10:46,960 --> 00:10:49,680
You don't even know how old he is.

169
00:10:50,120 --> 00:10:51,120
You only know how to scold him.

170
00:10:52,160 --> 00:10:53,160
Let me tell you,

171
00:10:53,840 --> 00:10:56,600
a good child grows with praises.

172
00:10:57,120 --> 00:10:58,200
Did I scold him wrongly?

173
00:10:59,600 --> 00:11:00,720
He spends money like water.

174
00:11:02,120 --> 00:11:04,160
He did not even know
how hard his parents earn money.

175
00:11:04,920 --> 00:11:06,197
He didn't do anything bad.

176
00:11:06,280 --> 00:11:08,480
He just went on a trip, didn't he?

177
00:11:08,960 --> 00:11:11,520
To read great books
and do great travels.

178
00:11:11,840 --> 00:11:13,520
Both knowledge and conduct
must be unified.

179
00:11:15,800 --> 00:11:17,040
I can tell.

180
00:11:17,160 --> 00:11:20,597
The older and younger
members of the family

181
00:11:20,680 --> 00:11:22,360
are all covering up and condoning him.

182
00:11:24,520 --> 00:11:25,520
You should say that

183
00:11:26,240 --> 00:11:27,600
to the elders

184
00:11:28,120 --> 00:11:29,120
in person.

185
00:11:31,800 --> 00:11:32,920
But then again,

186
00:11:33,520 --> 00:11:34,520
you said that

187
00:11:35,120 --> 00:11:36,520
our son didn't tell the truth.

188
00:11:36,960 --> 00:11:38,840
You should seriously

189
00:11:39,120 --> 00:11:40,520
reflect on yourself too.

190
00:11:41,120 --> 00:11:42,120
You always say,

191
00:11:42,480 --> 00:11:45,480
"Turn inward and examine yourself when
you encounter difficulties in life."

192
00:11:45,600 --> 00:11:46,600
Our son was just

193
00:11:47,280 --> 00:11:48,920
going on a trip,

194
00:11:49,280 --> 00:11:50,280
wasn't he?

195
00:11:50,480 --> 00:11:51,480
When he travelled,

196
00:11:51,680 --> 00:11:53,600
you called him a dude

197
00:11:54,240 --> 00:11:55,240
who's not aware of the hardships.

198
00:11:55,400 --> 00:11:58,517
You can't just let him
run off to work in the field

199
00:11:58,600 --> 00:12:00,077
whenever he's free
like you did when you were a kid.

200
00:12:00,160 --> 00:12:03,120
Moreover, we don't have
any field at home, do we?

201
00:12:06,480 --> 00:12:09,680
It's not like you don't know
how dignified your son is.

202
00:12:09,920 --> 00:12:11,120
You always scold him,

203
00:12:11,600 --> 00:12:13,520
will he dare to tell you
the truth in the future?

204
00:12:16,480 --> 00:12:18,120
It means it is my fault again.

205
00:12:18,480 --> 00:12:19,480
It's not like that.

206
00:12:20,520 --> 00:12:21,520
It's my fault.

207
00:12:21,960 --> 00:12:23,240
It's my fault.

208
00:12:23,800 --> 00:12:25,480
How can you both be at fault?

209
00:12:25,680 --> 00:12:27,520
I think I should squat there.

210
00:12:32,920 --> 00:12:33,920
Mr Ren.

211
00:12:35,840 --> 00:12:36,840
Professor Ren.

212
00:12:44,280 --> 00:12:48,240
Don't be angry after
you've had my cup of apologetic tea,

213
00:12:48,960 --> 00:12:50,680
I'll go and get them back.

214
00:12:55,240 --> 00:12:56,240
I get you some water.

215
00:13:03,520 --> 00:13:04,520
Tou Tou!

216
00:13:08,160 --> 00:13:09,160
Tou Tou has fainted.

217
00:13:15,520 --> 00:13:16,720
I'm okay.

218
00:13:26,280 --> 00:13:27,720
You're too weak.

219
00:13:29,480 --> 00:13:30,720
You prescribe two medications for her.

220
00:13:31,040 --> 00:13:32,360
Let us recuperate her
spleen and stomach first.

221
00:13:32,600 --> 00:13:34,280
After that,
let her drink aconite decoction.

222
00:13:35,520 --> 00:13:36,520
Her body is too cold.

223
00:13:36,920 --> 00:13:37,920
Stop drinking ice water.

224
00:13:39,840 --> 00:13:40,920
Get her a thermos.

225
00:13:43,520 --> 00:13:44,520
Well...

226
00:13:45,480 --> 00:13:46,480
Niece-in-law,

227
00:13:46,600 --> 00:13:49,600
I don't want
a pink-coloured Old Man Cup.

228
00:13:50,680 --> 00:13:51,800
I don't want pink colour, is it okay?

229
00:13:52,840 --> 00:13:54,280
I don't want yellow either.

230
00:13:55,800 --> 00:13:56,800
Is it okay?

231
00:14:00,880 --> 00:14:02,680
I don't want the cup
with a picture, is it okay?

232
00:14:23,920 --> 00:14:25,120
Why did you take on the blame for me?

233
00:14:31,920 --> 00:14:33,080
I'm envious of you.

234
00:14:35,120 --> 00:14:37,840
I don't envy you
for having everything you want.

235
00:14:39,680 --> 00:14:40,680
Well,

236
00:14:41,520 --> 00:14:42,680
every quarrel happened at home

237
00:14:43,360 --> 00:14:45,480
is because of you.

238
00:14:46,480 --> 00:14:48,240
Without you in the future,

239
00:14:49,800 --> 00:14:52,360
these elders must be bored every day.

240
00:14:52,960 --> 00:14:54,160
You're mindless.

241
00:14:54,360 --> 00:14:55,520
You're not answering my question.

242
00:14:59,800 --> 00:15:02,680
Your dad is so angry with you
because of a small mistake you made.

243
00:15:02,960 --> 00:15:04,160
But when I made a big mistake,

244
00:15:04,680 --> 00:15:06,040
your dad can forgive me.

245
00:15:07,800 --> 00:15:08,800
Do you know why?

246
00:15:09,360 --> 00:15:10,600
It's because you are his senior aunt.

247
00:15:13,480 --> 00:15:14,960
It's because your dad loves you.

248
00:15:17,520 --> 00:15:18,840
It's because that's your dad.

249
00:15:19,480 --> 00:15:20,480
He loves you.

250
00:15:23,120 --> 00:15:24,680
He has hope for you.

251
00:15:25,400 --> 00:15:26,800
He won't care too much

252
00:15:27,840 --> 00:15:29,240
whether I'm good or bad.

253
00:15:29,840 --> 00:15:32,520
All he has done for me
is to fulfill his duty.

254
00:15:32,920 --> 00:15:34,720
Well, it has nothing to do with you
taking the punishment for me.

255
00:15:38,280 --> 00:15:39,400
Oh, my grandson,

256
00:15:41,040 --> 00:15:44,160
I'm an orphan.

257
00:15:44,600 --> 00:15:46,480
No one puts hope in me.

258
00:15:46,920 --> 00:15:48,197
But you are different.

259
00:15:48,280 --> 00:15:50,240
You are the hope of your family.

260
00:15:51,280 --> 00:15:52,280
And

261
00:15:53,680 --> 00:15:55,360
I don't want to disappoint my master.

262
00:15:57,240 --> 00:15:58,840
So you have to work hard,

263
00:15:59,960 --> 00:16:00,960
do you understand?

264
00:16:02,120 --> 00:16:03,120
I have high hopes for you.

265
00:16:04,360 --> 00:16:05,360
Do you get me?

266
00:16:19,680 --> 00:16:21,360
But then again,

267
00:16:22,800 --> 00:16:23,800
you are right too.

268
00:16:25,160 --> 00:16:26,277
It's because I like to do the things

269
00:16:26,360 --> 00:16:27,360
that you're doing too.

270
00:16:27,720 --> 00:16:28,720
If I have money,

271
00:16:28,840 --> 00:16:29,960
I will do the same.

272
00:16:34,480 --> 00:16:35,840
But your dad is right too.

273
00:16:38,240 --> 00:16:40,480
So you both are right.

274
00:16:41,520 --> 00:16:43,960
It's perfect for me to take the blame.

275
00:16:59,360 --> 00:17:00,480
Hello.

276
